    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**2 - Importing Libraries**</span><br>\n",
    "\n",
    "This section includes all essential libraries required for data preprocessing, visualization, model building, evaluation, and deployment.\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **`os`** – for handling file paths, directories, and system-level operations  \n",
    "2. **`numpy`** – for efficient numerical operations and array manipulations  \n",
    "3. **`matplotlib.pyplot`** – for plotting graphs and visualizing training metrics  \n",
    "4. **`seaborn`** – for enhanced statistical data visualizations (heatmaps, etc.)  \n",
    "5. **`tensorflow`** – for building and training machine learning models  \n",
    "6. **`keras`** – high-level API in TensorFlow used to simplify model architecture  \n",
    "7. **`Sequential`** – to build models layer-by-layer in Keras  \n",
    "8. **`layers`** – contains essential building blocks like Rescaling, Pooling, Dense, etc.  \n",
    "9. **`optimizers` and `callbacks`** – for tuning model performance and training control  \n",
    "10. **`Layer`** – for creating custom layers (if needed)  \n",
    "11. **`EfficientNetV2B2`** – a pretrained model used for transfer learning  \n",
    "12. **`compute_class_weight`** – handles class imbalance by computing weights  \n",
    "13. **`confusion_matrix`, `classification_report`** – for model evaluation and diagnostics  \n",
    "14. **`gradio`** – to build an interactive web interface for your trained model  \n",
    "\n",
    "> ✅ These imports ensure that the project is fully equipped for preprocessing, training, evaluation, visualization, and deployment.\n"
   ]

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np  # Importing NumPy for numerical operations and array manipulations\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  # Importing Matplotlib for plotting graphs and visualizations\n",
    "import seaborn as sns  # Importing Seaborn for statistical data visualization, built on top of Matplotlib\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf  # Importing TensorFlow for building and training machine learning models\n",
    "from tensorflow import keras  # Importing Keras, a high-level API for TensorFlow, to simplify model building\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras import Layer  # Importing Layer class for creating custom layers in Keras\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential  # Importing Sequential model for building neural networks layer-by-layer\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Rescaling , GlobalAveragePooling2D\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras import layers, optimizers, callbacks  # Importing various modules for layers, optimizers, and callbacks in Keras\n",
    "from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight  # Importing function to compute class weights for imbalanced datasets\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.applications import EfficientNetV2B2  # Importing EfficientNetV2S model for transfer learning\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report  # Importing functions to evaluate model performance\n",
    "import gradio as gr  # Importing Gradio for creating interactive web interfaces for machine learning models"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2b15432",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**3 - Loading Data**</span><br>\n",
    "The Dataset i have used is from Kaggle.com [**Garbage Image Dataset**](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/farzadnekouei/trash-type-image-dataset) by Farzad Nekouei\n",
    "\n",
    "- This program loads the dataset from a directory and automatically splits it into **training (80%)** and **validation (20%)** subsets using `image_dataset_from_directory`.\n",
    "- The images are resized to **128×128** pixels and loaded in **batches of 32** for optimized memory and training performance.\n",
    "- The validation dataset is further divided into two equal parts to create a **validation set** and a **test set**.\n",
    "- Real-time performance optimization is applied to the test dataset using `cache()` and `prefetch()`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Libraries Used:** <br>\n",
    "1. `tensorflow.keras.utils` : for loading and splitting datasets  \n",
    "2. `tf.data` : for dataset cardinality, caching, and prefetching  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Functions & Parameters:**  \n",
    "1. `image_dataset_from_directory()` : loads image data with preprocessing and optional splitting  \n",
    "2. `validation_split` : splits the dataset into training and validation subsets  \n",
    "3. `subset=\"training\"/\"validation\"` : indicates which split to load  \n",
    "4. `image_size=(128, 128)` : resizes all images to the given size  \n",
    "5. `batch_size=32` : defines how many images to load per batch  \n",
    "6. `cardinality()` : gets number of batches to enable custom splitting  \n",
    "7. `take()` / `skip()` : used to split validation dataset into validation and test sets  \n",
    "8. `cache()` / `prefetch()` : boosts performance by preparing data ahead of time  \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "6df7201b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

    "dataset_dir= r\"D:\\Downloads\\SAM\\Edunet Internship\\Dataset\"\n",
    "\n",
    "image_size = (224, 224)\n",
    "batch_size = 32\n",
    "seed = 42\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load training dataset\n",
    "train_ds = tf.keras.utils.image_dataset_from_directory(\n",
    "    dataset_dir,\n",
    "    validation_split=0.2,\n",
    "    subset=\"training\",\n",
    "    seed=seed,\n",
    "    shuffle=True,\n",
    "    image_size=image_size,\n",
    "    batch_size=batch_size\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load validation dataset\n",
    "val_ds = tf.keras.utils.image_dataset_from_directory(\n",
    "    dataset_dir,\n",
    "    validation_split=0.2,\n",
    "    subset=\"validation\",\n",
    "    seed=seed,\n",
    "    shuffle=True,\n",
    "    image_size=image_size,\n",
    "    batch_size=batch_size\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get class names from validation dataset\n",
    "val_class = val_ds.class_names\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split validation into test and validation sets\n",
    "val_batches = tf.data.experimental.cardinality(val_ds)\n",
    "test_ds = val_ds.take(val_batches // 2)\n",
    "val_dat = val_ds.skip(val_batches // 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optimize test dataset\n",
    "test_ds_eval = test_ds.cache().prefetch(tf.data.AUTOTUNE)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ✨ Pretty output section\n",
    "print(\"\\nDataset Summary\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 30)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Class Names:\")\n",
    "for i, cls in enumerate(train_ds.class_names, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {i}. {cls}\")\n",
    "\n",

    "print(f\"Training Batches  : {len(train_ds)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation Batches: {len(val_dat)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test Batches      : {len(test_ds)}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 30)\n"
   ]

    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**5 - Enhanced Class Distribution Visualization**</span><br>\n",
    "\n",
    "This program computes and displays the class-wise image distribution across the training, validation, and test datasets. It ensures the dataset is balanced enough for fair model training and evaluation.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Purpose:**  \n",
    "  To calculate the percentage distribution of images per class and visualize the results to detect any imbalance that may affect model performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Steps Performed:**  \n",
    "  1. `count_distribution()` function iterates through each dataset to count label occurrences and convert them into percentages.  \n",
    "  2. `pandas.DataFrame` is used to display the class-wise percentages in a clean, tabular format.  \n",
    "  3. `simple_bar_plot()` function uses `matplotlib` to visually represent the distribution for each dataset.  \n",
    "  4. An `overall_dist` is computed by averaging training and validation distributions for a broader perspective.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Libraries Used:**  \n",
    "  1. `pandas` – for formatting the output as a readable table  \n",
    "  2. `matplotlib.pyplot` – for creating bar plots  \n",
    "  3. `tensorflow` – for handling the image datasets  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Functions Used:**  \n",
    "  - `count_distribution()` – counts and converts class occurrence to percentages  \n",
    "  - `simple_bar_plot()` – creates bar charts with consistent styling  \n",
    "  - `pd.DataFrame()` – organizes distribution data for display  \n",
    "  - `to_string()` – prints the DataFrame cleanly without index  \n",
    "\n",
    "> ✅ This step ensures your dataset is not only numerically balanced but also visually interpretable, helping you spot any class bias before training begins.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "cbc51278",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Class Distribution Summary:\n",
      "\n",
      "    Class  Train (%)  Validation (%)  Test (%)  Overall (%)\n",
      "cardboard      16.49           13.64     13.28        15.06\n",
      "    glass      19.69           20.16     20.31        19.93\n",
      "    metal      15.89           17.39     15.62        16.64\n",
      "    paper      23.49           24.31     21.48        23.90\n",
      "  plastic      19.35           17.79     21.09        18.57\n",
      "    trash       5.08            6.72      8.20         5.90\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "\n",
    "# Function to count class distribution (in %)\n",
    "def count_distribution(dataset, class_names):\n",
    "    total = 0\n",
    "    counts = {name: 0 for name in class_names}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for _, labels in dataset:\n",
    "        for label in labels.numpy():\n",
    "            counts[class_names[label]] += 1\n",
    "            total += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {k: round((v / total) * 100, 2) for k, v in counts.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Improved bar plot function with seaborn\n",
    "def simple_bar_plot(dist, title):\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "    sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    bars = plt.bar(dist.keys(), dist.values(), color=sns.color_palette(\"pastel\"), edgecolor='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add value labels on top\n",
    "    for bar in bars:\n",
    "        height = bar.get_height()\n",
    "        plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, height + 1, f'{height}%',\n",
    "                 ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.title(title, fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Percentage (%)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "    plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=10)\n",
    "    plt.ylim(0, 100)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get class names\n",
    "class_names = train_ds.class_names\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute distributions\n",
    "train_dist = count_distribution(train_ds, class_names)\n",
    "val_dist = count_distribution(val_ds, class_names)\n",
    "test_dist = count_distribution(test_ds, class_names)\n",
    "overall_dist = {k: round((train_dist[k] + val_dist[k]) / 2, 2) for k in class_names}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create DataFrame\n",
    "dist_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Class': class_names,\n",
    "    'Train (%)': [train_dist[k] for k in class_names],\n",
    "    'Validation (%)': [val_dist[k] for k in class_names],\n",
    "    'Test (%)': [test_dist[k] for k in class_names],\n",
    "    'Overall (%)': [overall_dist[k] for k in class_names],\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print clean table\n",
    "print(\"\\nClass Distribution Summary:\\n\")\n",
    "print(dist_df.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot distributions\n",
    "simple_bar_plot(train_dist, \"Training Set Class Distribution (%)\")\n",
    "simple_bar_plot(val_dist, \"Validation Set Class Distribution (%)\")\n",
    "simple_bar_plot(test_dist, \"Test Set Class Distribution (%)\")\n",
    "simple_bar_plot(overall_dist, \"Overall Class Distribution (%)\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2f443c2d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**6 - Calculating Class Weights to Handle Imbalance**</span><br>\n",
    "\n",
    "> This block handles imbalance in the dataset by assigning **weights** to each class based on its frequency in the training set. These weights will later help the model treat all classes fairly during training.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**  To compute class-wise weights so that underrepresented classes (like `trash`) are given more importance while training the model.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Steps Performed:**  \n",
    "  1. **Loop through `train_ds`** to count the number of samples per class and collect all labels.\n",
    "  2. Use **`compute_class_weight()`** to automatically calculate balanced class weights.\n",
    "  3. Create a dictionary mapping class index to its weight.\n",
    "  4. Display sample counts and computed weights with formatted output.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Libraries Used:**  \n",
    "  1. `sklearn.utils.class_weight` – for calculating balanced weights  \n",
    "  2. `numpy` – for label array handling and index alignment  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Functions Used:**  \n",
    "  - `compute_class_weight()` – computes inverse-frequency weights  \n",
    "  - `enumerate()` – used for mapping class indices  \n",
    "  - `round()` – used to display weights with readable precision  \n",
    "\n",
    "✅ These weights will be passed to `model.fit()` to help improve learning for rare classes and reduce prediction bias.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "c412e4b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "📊 Class Distribution in Training Set\n",
      "----------------------------------------\n",
      "0. cardboard  ➤ Samples: 334  | Weight: 1.011\n",
      "1. glass      ➤ Samples: 399  | Weight: 0.8463\n",
      "2. metal      ➤ Samples: 322  | Weight: 1.0487\n",
      "3. paper      ➤ Samples: 476  | Weight: 0.7094\n",
      "4. plastic    ➤ Samples: 392  | Weight: 0.8614\n",
      "5. trash      ➤ Samples: 103  | Weight: 3.2783\n",
      "----------------------------------------\n",
      "\n",
      "🧮 Total Training Samples: 2026\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Count class occurrences and collect all labels\n",
    "class_counts = {i: 0 for i in range(len(class_names))}\n",
    "all_labels = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for images, labels in train_ds:\n",
    "    for label in labels.numpy():\n",
    "        class_counts[label] += 1\n",
    "        all_labels.append(label)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute class weights (balanced)\n",
    "class_weights_array = compute_class_weight(\n",
    "    class_weight='balanced',\n",
    "    classes=np.arange(len(class_names)),\n",
    "    y=all_labels\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Map class index to weight\n",
    "class_weights = {i: round(w, 4) for i, w in enumerate(class_weights_array)}\n",
    "\n",
    "# ✨ Display results nicely\n",
    "print(\"\\n📊 Class Distribution in Training Set\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 40)\n",
    "for i, name in enumerate(class_names):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. {name:<10} ➤ Samples: {class_counts[i]:<4} | Weight: {class_weights[i]}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 40)\n",
    "print(f\"\\n🧮 Total Training Samples: {sum(class_counts.values())}\")\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cd3f43a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**7 - Preprocessing and Model Training**</span><br>\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    ">This section outlines the complete training pipeline using **EfficientNetV2B2** as the backbone model, incorporating class imbalance handling, progress logging, and performance visualization.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data Augmentation** - \n",
    "Applies real-time transformations to improve model generalization:\n",
    "\n",
    "    - Horizontal flip\n",
    "    - Random rotation\n",
    "    - Random zoom\n",
    "    - Random contrast\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Model Architecture** - A `Sequential` model with the following components:\n",
    "\n",
    "    - **EfficientNetV2B2** (pretrained on ImageNet, `include_top=False`)\n",
    "    - First **100 layers frozen** to preserve learned features\n",
    "    - `GlobalAveragePooling2D` layer to reduce feature dimensions\n",
    "    - `Dropout(0.3)` to reduce overfitting\n",
    "    - Final `Dense(6, activation='softmax')` layer for 6-class prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Loss & Optimizer**\n",
    "\n",
    "    - Optimizer: `Adam` (with learning rate = 1e-4)\n",
    "    - Loss Function: `sparse_categorical_crossentropy` (for integer labels)\n",
    "    - Metrics: `accuracy`\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Callbacks Used**\n",
    "\n",
    "    - `EarlyStopping`: Stops training if `val_loss` doesn't improve for 3 epochs  \n",
    "    - `ModelCheckpoint`: Saves the best model (based on `val_accuracy`) to **`best_model.keras`**\n",
    "    - `TqdmCallback`: Shows a live progress bar for each epoch in the terminal\n",
    "\n",
    "5. **Training Settings**\n",
    "\n",
    "    - Epochs: `15`\n",
    "    - Batch Size: `32`\n",
    "    - Uses `class_weights` to balance underrepresented classes\n",
    "    - Trains on `train_ds`, validates on `val_ds`\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "6. **Post-training Outputs**\n",
    "\n",
    "    - ✅ Saves the **best model** in `.keras` format  \n",
    "    - ✅ Stores training history (`loss`, `accuracy`, etc.) in a **`.pkl` file** using `pickle`  \n",
    "    - ✅ Displays a **Pandas table** of training metrics after training  \n",
    "    - ✅ Plots **accuracy** and **loss** graphs for both training and validation over epochs\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Unified Model Training Pipeline with 128x128 Image Input and Enhanced Output\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from tqdm.keras import TqdmCallback\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras import layers, optimizers, callbacks\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import GlobalAveragePooling2D\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.applications import EfficientNetV2B2\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data Augmentation\n",
    "data_augmentation = Sequential([\n",
    "    layers.RandomFlip(\"horizontal\"),\n",
    "    layers.RandomRotation(0.1),\n",
    "    layers.RandomZoom(0.1),\n",
    "    layers.RandomContrast(0.1),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load Pretrained EfficientNetV2B2 with matching input size\n",
    "base_model = EfficientNetV2B2(\n",
    "    include_top=False,\n",
    "    input_shape=(224, 224, 3),\n",
    "    include_preprocessing=True,\n",
    "    weights='imagenet'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Freeze early layers\n",
    "base_model.trainable = True\n",
    "for layer in base_model.layers[:100]:\n",
    "    layer.trainable = False\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build Final Model\n",
    "model = Sequential([\n",
    "    layers.Input(shape=(224, 224, 3)),\n",
    "    data_augmentation,\n",
    "    base_model,\n",
    "    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),\n",
    "    layers.Dropout(0.3),\n",
    "    layers.Dense(6, activation='softmax')\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compile Model\n",
    "model.compile(\n",
    "    optimizer=optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-4),\n",
    "    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
    "    metrics=['accuracy']\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Callbacks\n",
    "early = callbacks.EarlyStopping(\n",
    "    monitor='val_loss',\n",
    "    patience=3,\n",
    "    restore_best_weights=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "checkpoint = callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(\n",
    "    filepath='best_model224.keras',\n",
    "    monitor='val_accuracy',\n",
    "    save_best_only=True,\n",
    "    mode='max',\n",
    "    verbose=1\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pre-training Summary\n",
    "epochs = 15\n",
    "print(\"\\n📦 Starting Model Training...\")\n",
    "print(f\"Epochs       : {epochs}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Class Weights: {class_weights}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Checkpoint   : Best model saved to 'best_model224.keras'\")\n",
    "print(f\"Early Stop   : Enabled with patience=3\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the Model with Tqdm progress bar\n",
    "history = model.fit(\n",
    "    train_ds,\n",
    "    validation_data=val_ds,\n",
    "    epochs=epochs,\n",
    "    class_weight=class_weights,\n",
    "    batch_size=32,\n",
    "    callbacks=[early, checkpoint, TqdmCallback(verbose=1)]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display training log as a table\n",
    "df_log = pd.DataFrame(history.history)\n",
    "print(\"\\n📊 Training Log Summary:\")\n",
    "print(df_log.to_string(index=True))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save history for later comparison\n",
    "with open(\"history224.pkl\", \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    pickle.dump(history.history, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Accuracy and Loss Graphs\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Accuracy\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Train Acc', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Val Acc', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Accuracy Over Epochs')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loss\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Train Loss', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Val Loss', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Loss Over Epochs')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

       "\u001b[1m Non-trainable params: \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;34m803,186\u001b[0m (3.06 MB)\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Find the base model layer by layer name or type\n",
    "for layer in model.layers:\n",
    "    if isinstance(layer, tf.keras.Model) and \"efficientnetv2b2\" in layer.name.lower():\n",
    "        base_model = layer\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print summary of the extracted base model\n",
    "base_model.summary()\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "ec5481d4",

     "name": "stdout",

      "   cardboard       1.00      0.94      0.97        35\n",
      "       glass       0.94      0.92      0.93        52\n",
      "       metal       0.94      0.98      0.96        46\n",
      "       paper       0.95      1.00      0.97        53\n",
      "     plastic       0.98      0.96      0.97        48\n",
      "       trash       1.00      0.95      0.98        22\n",
      "\n",
      "    accuracy                           0.96       256\n",

    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x800 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate_model(model_path, test_dataset, class_names):\n",
    "    # Load the model\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nLoading Model: {model_path}\")\n",
    "    model = tf.keras.models.load_model(model_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Evaluate on test set\n",
    "    print(\"\\nEvaluating Model on Test Dataset...\\n\" + \"-\"*50)\n",
    "    loss, accuracy = model.evaluate(test_dataset, verbose=0)\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Test Accuracy : {accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"📉 Test Loss     : {loss:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(\"-\"*50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # True and predicted labels\n",
    "    y_true = np.concatenate([labels.numpy() for _, labels in test_dataset])\n",
    "    y_pred_probs = model.predict(test_dataset, verbose=0)\n",
    "    y_pred = np.argmax(y_pred_probs, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Classification Report\n",
    "    print(\"\\n📊 Classification Report:\\n\" + \"-\"*50)\n",
    "    report = classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=class_names)\n",
    "    print(report)\n",
    "    print(\"-\"*50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Confusion Matrix\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot Confusion Matrix\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "    sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"YlGnBu\", linewidths=.5,\n",
    "                xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix\", fontsize=16)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Predicted Labels\", fontsize=12)\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"True Labels\", fontsize=12)\n",
    "    plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "    plt.yticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 🧪 Example usage\n",
    "evaluate_model(\"best_model_finetuned224.keras\", test_ds_eval, class_names)\n"
   ]
  },
  {

       "<Figure size 1800x800 with 8 Axes>"

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load your trained model\n",
    "model_path = 'best_model_finetuned224.keras'  # Change if needed\n",
    "model = tf.keras.models.load_model(model_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get class names from training dataset\n",
    "class_names = train_ds.class_names  \n",
    "\n",
    "# Shuffle test dataset before sampling\n",
    "test_ds_eval_shuffled = test_ds_eval.shuffle(1000, reshuffle_each_iteration=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take one random batch from test dataset and predict\n",
    "for images, labels in test_ds_eval_shuffled.take(1):  \n",
    "    predictions = model.predict(images)  \n",
    "    pred_labels = tf.argmax(predictions, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot first 8 images with predictions\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(18, 8))\n",
    "    for i in range(8):\n",
    "        plt.subplot(2, 4, i + 1)\n",
    "        plt.imshow(images[i].numpy().astype(\"uint8\"))\n",
    "        true_cls = class_names[labels[i]]\n",
    "        pred_cls = class_names[pred_labels[i]]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Green if correct, red if wrong\n",
    "        title_color = 'green' if true_cls == pred_cls else 'red'\n",
    "        plt.title(f\"True: {true_cls}\\nPred: {pred_cls}\", color=title_color, fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')  # ← increased font size here\n",
    "        plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.suptitle(f\"Model Predictions from '{model_path}'\", fontsize=22, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.95])\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#  Retraining Pipeline with Accuracy Comparison and Conditional Saving + Custom CNN Layers\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from tqdm.keras import TqdmCallback\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras import optimizers, callbacks, layers, models\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Load the previously saved model\n",
    "old_model_path = 'best_model224.keras'\n",
    "model_save_path = 'best_model_finetuned224.keras'\n",
    "\n",
    "old_model = tf.keras.models.load_model(old_model_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Evaluate old model on validation set\n",
    "val_images, val_labels = [], []\n",
    "for x, y in val_ds.unbatch():\n",
    "    val_images.append(x.numpy())\n",
    "    val_labels.append(y.numpy())\n",
    "\n",
    "val_images = np.stack(val_images)\n",
    "val_labels = np.array(val_labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "old_preds = old_model.predict(val_images, verbose=0)\n",
    "old_pred_labels = np.argmax(old_preds, axis=1)\n",
    "old_val_accuracy = accuracy_score(val_labels, old_pred_labels)\n",
    "print(f\"📏 Old Model Accuracy: {old_val_accuracy*100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Extract the EfficientNetV2B2 base model from the saved model\n",
    "base_model = None\n",
    "for layer in old_model.layers:\n",
    "    if isinstance(layer, tf.keras.Model) and 'efficientnet' in layer.name:\n",
    "        base_model = layer\n",
    "        break\n",
    "if base_model is None:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(\"EfficientNetV2B2 base model not found inside loaded model.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Unfreeze some deeper layers for fine-tuning\n",
    "base_model.trainable = True\n",
    "for layer in base_model.layers[:75]:\n",
    "    layer.trainable = False\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Create new model with added custom CNN layers\n",
    "model = models.Sequential([\n",
    "    layers.Input(shape=(224, 224, 3)),\n",
    "    base_model,\n",
    "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same'),\n",
    "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
    "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same'),\n",
    "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
    "    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),\n",
    "    layers.Dropout(0.4),\n",
    "    layers.Dense(6, activation='softmax')\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Compile the model\n",
    "model.compile(\n",
    "    optimizer=optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-5),\n",
    "    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
    "    metrics=['accuracy']\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Custom callback to conditionally save improved models\n",
    "class ConditionalSave(tf.keras.callbacks.Callback):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, initial_best, filename):\n",
    "        self.best_accuracy = initial_best\n",
    "        self.filename = filename\n",
    "\n",
    "    def on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs=None):\n",
    "        val_acc = logs.get(\"val_accuracy\")\n",
    "        if val_acc and val_acc > self.best_accuracy:\n",
    "            print(f\"\\n💾 Improved! New Val Acc: {val_acc:.4f} > Prev Best: {self.best_accuracy:.4f}. Saving as '{self.filename}'...\")\n",
    "            self.model.save(self.filename)\n",
    "            self.best_accuracy = val_acc\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Callbacks\n",
    "early = callbacks.EarlyStopping(\n",
    "    monitor='val_loss',\n",
    "    patience=10,\n",
    "    restore_best_weights=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Fine-tuning Info\n",
    "epochs = 50\n",
    "print(\"\\n🔁 Fine-Tuning EfficientNetV2B2 + Custom CNN...\")\n",
    "print(f\"🔓 Unfroze layers after 75\")\n",
    "print(f\"🎯 Previous Validation Accuracy: {old_val_accuracy*100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"💾 Will save only if validation accuracy improves over previous\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Train\n",
    "history = model.fit(\n",
    "    train_ds,\n",
    "    validation_data=val_ds,\n",
    "    epochs=epochs,\n",
    "    class_weight=class_weights,\n",
    "    batch_size=32,\n",
    "    callbacks=[\n",
    "        early,\n",
    "        TqdmCallback(verbose=1),\n",
    "        ConditionalSave(initial_best=old_val_accuracy, filename=model_save_path)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Save history\n",
    "with open(\"history_finetuned224.pkl\", \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    pickle.dump(history.history, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Show Log Table\n",
    "df_log = pd.DataFrame(history.history)\n",
    "print(\"\\n📊 Fine-tuning Log Summary:\")\n",
    "print(df_log.to_string(index=True))\n",
    "\n",
    "#  Plot Training Curves\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Train Acc', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Val Acc', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Fine-tuning Accuracy Over Epochs')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Train Loss', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Val Loss', marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('Fine-tuning Loss Over Epochs')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# === Paths ===\n",
    "model_path = 'best_model_finetuned224.keras'     \n",
    "history_path = 'history_finetuned224.pkl'         \n",
    "\n",
    "# === Load the model ===\n",
    "model = tf.keras.models.load_model(model_path)\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded model from: {model_path}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# === Load history ===\n",
    "with open(history_path, 'rb') as f:\n",
    "    history = pickle.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "# === Get final epoch metrics ===\n",
    "final_accuracy     = history['accuracy'][-1]\n",
    "final_val_accuracy = history['val_accuracy'][-1]\n",
    "final_loss         = history['loss'][-1]\n",
    "final_val_loss     = history['val_loss'][-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n📊 Final Training Summary:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Train Accuracy     : {final_accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation Accuracy: {final_val_accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Train Loss         : {final_loss:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation Loss    : {final_val_loss:.4f}\")\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b7429264",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### <span style=\"color:red\">**Comparing Model Performance: Accuracy & Loss Trends**</span><br>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "49b5d384",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_model_history(history_file, model_name=\"Model\"):\n",
    "    # Load training history from a .pkl file\n",
    "    with open(history_file, \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "        history = pickle.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "    acc = history['accuracy']\n",
    "    val_acc = history['val_accuracy']\n",
    "    loss = history['loss']\n",
    "    val_loss = history['val_loss']\n",
    "    epochs_range = range(len(acc))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Set up plots\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Accuracy Plot ---\n",
    "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(epochs_range, acc, label='Train Acc', color='green', marker='o')\n",
    "    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_acc, label='Val Acc', color='blue', marker='s', linestyle='--')\n",
    "    plt.title(f'📈 Accuracy - {model_name}')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
    "    plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "    plt.legend(loc='lower right')\n",
    "    plt.xticks(epochs_range)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Loss Plot ---\n",
    "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "    plt.plot(epochs_range, loss, label='Train Loss', color='red', marker='o')\n",
    "    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_loss, label='Val Loss', color='orange', marker='s', linestyle='--')\n",
    "    plt.title(f'📉 Loss - {model_name}')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
    "    plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "    plt.legend(loc='upper right')\n",
    "    plt.xticks(epochs_range)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Layout & show\n",
    "    plt.suptitle(f\"📊 Training Summary for {model_name}\", fontsize=16, y=1.05)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   ],
   "source": [
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import load_model\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.applications.efficientnet_v2 import preprocess_input\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import gradio as gr\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load your trained model\n",
    "model = load_model(\"best_model_finetuned224.keras\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Class labels\n",
    "class_names = ['Cardboard', 'Glass', 'Metal', 'Paper', 'Plastic', 'Trash']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classify image and return top prediction with styled output\n",
    "def classify_image(img):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        if img is None:\n",
    "            return \"<div style='color:red;'>No image received. Please upload or capture an image.</div>\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        img = img.resize((224, 224))\n",
    "        img_array = np.array(img, dtype=np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if img_array.shape != (224, 224, 3):\n",
    "            return f\"<div style='color:red;'>Unexpected input shape: {img_array.shape}</div>\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        img_array = preprocess_input(img_array)\n",
    "        img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)\n",
    "        prediction = model.predict(img_array)[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        predicted_class_index = np.argmax(prediction)\n",
    "        predicted_class_name = class_names[predicted_class_index]\n",
    "        confidence = float(prediction[predicted_class_index])\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Return styled HTML result\n",
    "        return f\"\"\"\n",
    "        <div style='text-align: center; font-size: 28px; font-weight: bold; color: #00FFAA; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;'>\n",
    "            Prediction: {predicted_class_name}<br>\n",
    "            <span style='font-size: 20px; color: #888;'>Confidence: {confidence:.2%}</span>\n",
    "        </div>\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        return f\"<div style='color:red;'>Error during prediction: {str(e)}</div>\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gradio interface with webcam and upload support\n",
    "iface = gr.Interface(\n",
    "    fn=classify_image,\n",
    "    inputs=gr.Image(type=\"pil\", sources=[\"upload\", \"webcam\"],),  #\n",
    "    outputs=gr.HTML(),\n",
    "    title=\"♻️ Waste Material Classifier\",\n",
    "    description=\"Upload or capture an image and this AI model will classify it into one of six recyclable waste categories.\",\n",
    "    article=\"\"\"\n",
    "    <br><br>\n",
    "    <div style='display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 60px; color: #b0b0b0; font-size: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap;'>\n",
    "        <div>Powered by EfficientNetV2</div>\n",
    "        <div>Built with TensorFlow and Gradio</div>\n",
    "    </div>\n",
    "    <div style='text-align: center; color: #b0b0b0; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 10px; font-family: monospace'>\n",
    "        Developed by Saaiem Salaar\n",
    "        <br>\n",
    "        <a href='https://github.com/Salaar-Saaiem' target='_blank' style='margin: 0 8px; display: inline-block;'>\n",
    "            <img src='https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/25/25231.png' width='20' height='20' alt='GitHub' style='vertical-align: middle;' />\n",
    "        </a>\n",
    "        <a href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/salaarsaaiem525/' target='_blank' style='margin: 0 8px; display: inline-block;'>\n",
    "            <img src='https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/174/174857.png' width='20' height='20' alt='LinkedIn' style='vertical-align: middle;' />\n",
    "        </a>\n",
    "    </div>\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "iface.launch(share=True)\n"
   ]
  }
